<subSubSection id="88AC157974BAE17DB41E675CFEE1D671" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="ED2730ACE3BC3DC210FFA639DA9433DD" pageId="7" pageNumber="28">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A0D9D2F4A48411391BF766544C79CA94" pageId="7" pageNumber="28">
The new species differs from all congeners by having the dorsal-and caudal-fin tips whitish (Fig. 4) (vs. entirely dark). It further differs from 
<taxonomicName id="6647D55D453E72155951EA1555EA98C0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudancistrus reus" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="reus">Pseudancistrus reus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0BCAEDAFBB45FC3046451F39F8E5F6DC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudancistrus kayabi" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kayabi">Pseudancistrus kayabi</taxonomicName>
by having conspicuous whitish spots on the body (vs. body mottled or with bars in 
<taxonomicName id="5C0733839D3A4AED5A6B8645D9598DC9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudancistrus reus" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="reus">Pseudancistrus reus</taxonomicName>
and with whitish spots that fade along the body and can cover more than one plate in 
<taxonomicName id="EB45EAEE4BC147F0BA9207F896A8BFCE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudancistrus kayabi" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kayabi">Pseudancistrus kayabi</taxonomicName>
). It is also distinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="20823CE9E98CB7EF79415CF2CFDBEF9F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudancistrus depressus" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="depressus">Pseudancistrus depressus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="895233E8CB03B52BB01B9D8663B8C3F3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudancistrus barbatus" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="barbatus">Pseudancistrus barbatus</taxonomicName>
by having the snout with yellowish odontodes (vs. reddish-brown) (see Fig. 3 in 
<bibRefCitation id="87513E21C4C9D6E31165D9C4162F4294" author="De Chambrier, S" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="11" pageNumber="32" pagination="45 - 58" title="Pseudancistruscorantijniensis, a new species from the Guyana Shield (Siluriformes: Loricariidae) with a molecular and morphological description of the Pseudancistrusbarbatus group." volume="1918" year="2008">De Chambrier and Montoya-Burgos 2008</bibRefCitation>
for comparison) and from 
<taxonomicName id="E168D5709427AE83D0F5F5C6FC0682B6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudancistrus nigrescens" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrescens">Pseudancistrus nigrescens</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DB30F8C813C3DCA2464A42AEE678F91F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudancistrus corantijniensis" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="corantijniensis">Pseudancistrus corantijniensis</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="54B49DE49D5D3ED6B80D35B84C8CC028" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudancistrus zawadzkii" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zawadzkii">Pseudancistrus zawadzkii</taxonomicName>
by having smaller whitish spots covering the body which increase gradually in size on the head (diameter 0.3−0.8 mm) and further on the body (diameter 0.7−1.3) (vs. spots abruptly increasing size between the head (diameter 1.1−1.3) and the body (diameter 2.6−2.3 mm). In addition, the new species is distinguished by a shorter predorsal length, 39−43% SL (vs. 43−46% in 
<taxonomicName id="9BB38FBA1D28B9F6393F0A67E0BF3283" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudancistrus zawadzkii" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zawadzkii">Pseudancistrus zawadzkii</taxonomicName>
and 43−45% in 
<taxonomicName id="A9F6C9B4F8D1AA33C316AD8F30AE9D57" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudancistrus nigrescens" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrescens">Pseudancistrus nigrescens</taxonomicName>
), a smaller dorsal pectoral depth, 23−27% SL (vs. 27−31% in 
<taxonomicName id="988095C0BFC4A2468439A91E24462B0A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudancistrus zawadzkii" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zawadzkii">Pseudancistrus zawadzkii</taxonomicName>
); a smaller caudal peduncle depth, 9−11% SL (vs. 13−14% in 
<taxonomicName id="A354BF06613C5697BF15871269460484" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudancistrus zawadzkii" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zawadzkii">Pseudancistrus zawadzkii</taxonomicName>
and 13% in 
<taxonomicName id="64C8585FFF2A2354BE400AAFC212F7E9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudancistrus nigrescens" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrescens">Pseudancistrus nigrescens</taxonomicName>
), a shorter barbel, 5−9% HL (vs. 10−11 in 
<taxonomicName id="2F79D577B4F2DC7EA5F5DEE06ED933BE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudancistrus nigrescens" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrescens">Pseudancistrus nigrescens</taxonomicName>
), and head depth, 57−66% SL, which is smaller than in 
<taxonomicName id="ADC075A8E8F8D6E829A298CD281BE58C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pseudancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudancistrus zawadzkii" order="Siluriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zawadzkii">Pseudancistrus zawadzkii</taxonomicName>
(67−73%) but greater than in 
